    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const {\n  opportunityName, accountName, opportunityOwner, opportunityAmount, opportunityCloseDate,\n  opportunityStatus, recentActivity, engagedPeople, situationSearch\n} = $json;\n\nconst prompt = `You are an AI revenue agent analyzing a deal using Backstory (People.ai) signal data.\n\nDeal: ${opportunityName}\nAccount: ${accountName}\nOwner: ${opportunityOwner || 'Unknown'}\nAmount: ${opportunityAmount ? '$' + Number(opportunityAmount).toLocaleString() : 'Unknown'}\nClose Date: ${opportunityCloseDate || 'Unknown'}\n\n## Opportunity Status & Risk Signals\n${opportunityStatus || 'No status data available'}\n\n## Recent Activity (last 30 days)\n${recentActivity || 'No recent activity recorded'}\n\n## Engaged Stakeholders\n${engagedPeople || 'No engagement data available'}\n\n## Similar Situations (Situation Search)\n${situationSearch || 'No similar situations found'}\n\nYour job: reason over this data like an experienced sales leader and produce a Slack-formatted deal risk brief.\n\nOutput format:\n:rotating_light: *Deal Risk Brief — ${opportunityName}*\n\n*Risk Summary* — top 3 risk signals with severity (High/Med/Low)\n\n*Stakeholder Coverage* — who is engaged, who is missing, what that means\n\n*What Similar Deals Did* — 2-3 Situation Search examples and the tactics that worked\n\n*Recommended Next Actions* — 3 specific, time-bound actions for the rep this week\n\nBe direct. Flag the biggest risk first. Use Slack mrkdwn (*bold*, • bullets).`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { opportunityName, accountName, prompt } }];"
      },
